Exciting news!! Jess @casa.de.stela and Eryn @flowersbyeryn are beyond thrilled to share with you that our two brands will soon share space in the Mill District at 635 NW Colorado (right next to @palatecoffee). 

We were introduced over a year ago by our dear mutual friend @lilmill who encouraged us to meet and talk about our shared vision to create a special little place in Bend. Countless coffee dates, brainstorming meetings, and shared Pinterest visions later we were lucky enough to find and secure the lovely little house previously occupied by @lostseasonsupply (thank you @stumpmunkfarms and @compass !). 

Around the corner from Eryn's current shop and a block away from Jess's home, this space is the perfect opportunity to expand on both of our businesses and for Jess to finally set up roots again in her new hometown. With luscious seasonal flower designs, gorgeously designed and sourced clothing, beautiful ceramics, and unique local, West Coast and global items mixed with lots of opportunity for community connection through workshops and artisan pop-ups, we cannot wait to open the doors to @thebungalowbend to you!!! 

@casa.de.stela is planning a soft opening for this Friday 4/14 from 3-8pm and Saturday 4/15 from 10am-6pm, and @flowersbyeryn will be open in the shared space beginning May 2nd (more details to follow). Plus, stay tuned for a "GRAND OPENING" event soon. 

Thank you so much for your support over the years and we can't wait to embark on this new chapter with you all. xo - Jess & Eryn

Heartbreak comes in so many different shapes and forms. Today we’re experiencing the lost of one of the truly “best boys” around. Gruner was my protector, best buddy and the king of keeping me inline. Like no other dog I’ve ever met, he had a sense of self and calmness that immediately gained respect wherever we went. My dad often referred to him as Joe because clearly Gruner was a last name. Joe Gruner lived many lives in my dad’s stories and in actuality. From Guatemala to LA to Guatemala and up to Oregon, he’s always been along for the ride. He saw me through relationships heartbreak, business challenges and my cancer struggles. He kept @jackiknight__ and I warm when we hiked a volcano and made me uncomfortably warm when he refused to sleep anywhere other than on my feet at night. Gingie and I are going to be lost for a little while without this guy. ❤️

This time last year, one of my best friends @josephinepulitano and I pulled of the trip of a lifetime to Georgia O’Keeffe’s longtime home in Abiquiu, New Mexico. My mom @pambusyb and I drove 20 hours each way with Gruner and Ginger. One of my favorite road trips to date. Our stop in Moab was unreal. 
Jo and I had dreamed up this trip about 8 months beforehand and found a magical property @theland.earth in Abiquiu that sits of 40 acres and would be perfect for a retreat. With this, or first ever US craft and culture trip was launched. With a focus on painting, plant dyed and private museum tour. We had the most beautiful group of friends, family, past retreat friends and new faces. It’s moments like these that remind me of the power of community and female friendships. 🌵🌵🌵

So the story goes, my grandmother happened upon a fallen tree while living in Italy and commissioned two tables for my father’s childhood home. One being narrower than the two - the children’s table and the larger, the adult table. We grew up with the smaller table in our home, often used as a side table until we had space to dine at an 11 foot long table in the house we moved into when I was 16. After my grandmother passed a few years ago, we inherited the “adult” table and the “children’s” table was sent to my uncle in Connecticut. Sadly for my parents, the table never fit in their new home in Bend and fortunately for me, it fit perfectly in my new shop. I always love the stories family heirlooms carry and to have part of my own family history makes @thebungalowbend ‘s decor feel that much more special ❤️

🌟 Reintroducing Myself to the Casa de Stela Family 🌟
Hey there, lovely souls! 👋 It's been a few years and I thought it's high time I reacquaint myself with all of you amazing people. I'm Jess, the proud owner and founder of Casa de Stela since 2010, and I'm bursting with excitement to reconnect and share my journey with you.

🔍 A Bit About Me:

🌍 I began my career as an archaeologist, delving into the mysteries of ancient Mesoamerica, which led me down to Guatemala for the first time. It was an adventure I'll never forget, and it set the stage for my love of creativity and discovery.

🌴 In 2010 I started Stela 9 as an accessories company with ethical production based in Guatemala and India. For the first 6 years we sold wholesale to hundreds of small boutiques and larger companies like Urban Outfitters, Revolve, Free People and Anthropologie.

Our knits are crafted with love and care by our incredible artisan partners in Puno, Peru. When you treat yourself to one of our lux knits you’re not only supporting our female owned business but also allowing us to continue to contribute to their production cycle annually. 🦙❤️

2023 was quite the year for Casa de Stela ❤️ It was the continuation of our very first knitwear line, which has become our best selling product. It was the year we really established our ceramics and signature style - daisies + Klein blue 🌀 (second best selling product). Stela Travel took us to Guatemala twice 🇬🇹 and we opened a damn store!!!! 😅 @thebungalowbend in Bend, Oregon.  I learned a lot in the past year about my business and myself and can’t wait to keep pushing the envelope in 2024 ✨ None of this would be possible without your support! I am so incredibly grateful that you’ve allowed Casa de Stela to thrive for the past 13 years and can’t wait to share what I have planned for this year ✨
